Here’s a clear, professional, no-excuses, priority-focused version you can send to your manager. It explains the situation honestly and shows accountability without sounding defensive:

⸻

Hi [Manager’s Name],

I wanted to give some context on the limited progress with the Jest framework work. Over the last few weeks, my focus has been on completing the February release stories up until code freeze, alongside the release version upgrade—both of which were top-priority and time-sensitive.

After the freeze, we moved straight into the Angular version update and addressing the resulting defects, which has continued to require immediate attention. Because of these parallel priorities, I haven’t yet had a clear window to start the Jest framework work.

Now that the Angular update is stabilizing, I can plan dedicated time to begin work on Jest and provide a more concrete update going forward.

Please let me know if you’d like me to reprioritize or break this into smaller milestones.

Thanks,
Subha

