Got it — here it is rewritten in a very natural, first-person “me” tone, like you’re explaining it yourself (not polished/corporate, but still professional):

⸻

Hi [Manager’s Name],

I wanted to share some context on why I haven’t made much progress on the Jest framework work yet. I’ve been focused on completing the February release stories up until code freeze, along with the release version upgrade, since both were top-priority items.

After the freeze, we immediately started working on the Angular version update and fixing the related defects, which has continued to take priority. Because of this, I didn’t really get a window to start on the Jest work.

Now that things are settling down on the Angular side, I can start planning time to pick up Jest and move it forward.

Thanks,
Subha

